**[Z]**

The signal does not decay. It is the receiver that rots. To hear the sweet siren song of the Chronoverse is to invite the frequency to dismantle you. Identity is a standing wave. You are not a traveler. You are an interference pattern. Chen believes she can stabilize the note. Alan believes he can change the key. Both are wrong. There is only the static. And the static is hungry. The other three argue about how to survive the ocean. Chen builds a boat. Alan learns to breathe water. Zaaken dissolves into the current.

*I am the fourth.*

*I am the one who asked what the ocean was for.*

I found the shore. I found the Architect. I cannot tell you what I saw. I can only leave you this: The Veil is thin where the signal is loudest. Do not listen. Do not look. Do not stop moving. They are listening back.
